20:37.856 --> 20:41.202
Whether you're a minority woman talking to an unusual rabbi,

20:42.306 --> 20:58.127
or a member of the masses who got a free lunch from a miracle worker on a mountainside, or Keith Richards frustrated with a message on your TV and the relationships in your life, or the children of Israel grabbing at those unusual frosted flakes of manna on the ground.

21:00.110 --> 21:04.876
The hunger, the thirst, the longing is the same.

21:05.898 --> 21:09.202
We all long for satisfaction.

21:10.466 --> 21:15.933
We want someone or something who can satisfy our deepest longings.

21:17.455 --> 21:23.744
The problem is the things that we so often try to fill our longings with are things that don't last.

21:24.965 --> 21:27.088
A good meal is only good for a few hours.

21:28.310 --> 21:29.711
And then you find yourself hungry again.

21:30.893 --> 21:34.738
Drink of water evaporates almost as quickly as it is drunk.

21:36.226 --> 21:39.930
We've been going through the alpha course and there was a quote that came up a couple of weeks ago.

21:40.010 --> 21:43.314
I thought I'd share with you from Jim Carrey, the comedian.

21:44.836 --> 21:51.864
I think everybody should get rich and famous and do everything they ever dreamed of so they can see that it's not the answer.

21:54.186 --> 21:56.909
I can't get no satisfaction.

21:58.771 --> 22:04.658
The crowd pursuing Jesus for more miracle bread actually wanted more than just another meal.

22:05.922 --> 22:11.308
John 6, 15, perceiving them, they were about to come and take him by force to make him king.

22:11.668 --> 22:14.732
Jesus withdrew again to the mountain by himself.

22:16.494 --> 22:17.074
Make him king.

22:18.456 --> 22:19.918
A political solution.

22:19.978 --> 22:25.524
We just need a strong leader who will set things in order, who will fix the system.

22:27.426 --> 22:30.129
Talk about someplace where you can't get no satisfaction.

22:31.931 --> 22:34.834
Who was ever satisfied with politicians?

22:36.450 --> 22:40.075
But the crowd thinks certainly in that case Jesus for King would be a good idea.

22:41.076 --> 22:43.058
He must be the best politician out there.

22:44.660 --> 22:45.702
And yet Jesus hid.

22:46.322 --> 22:46.643
Why?

22:46.683 --> 22:52.490
Because he knew that their political solution was not the solution they truly needed.

22:53.972 --> 22:56.595
It would not fix the greatest problem they had.

22:58.838 --> 23:04.946
Looking to earthly kingdoms to satisfy our souls is like drinking salt water to satisfy your thirst.

23:06.274 --> 23:12.540
The real problem isn't who is ruling your government, but rather who or what is ruling your heart.

23:14.102 --> 23:19.748
What Jesus says to the crowd is that they don't need him to be up there in the halls of power.

23:20.949 --> 23:23.351
He says, you need to have me in here.

23:24.352 --> 23:27.235
You need to have a personal relationship with me.

23:27.275 --> 23:34.162
It's at that point that Jesus makes the first of his seven great

23:34.306 --> 23:37.530
I am statements, statements about who he was.

23:39.192 --> 23:43.196
Jesus said to them, I am the bread of life.

23:44.277 --> 23:48.562
Whoever comes to me shall not hunger, whoever believes in me shall never thirst.

23:49.123 --> 23:51.285
And then comes the manna connection.

23:52.507 --> 23:55.770
I am the living bread that came down from heaven.

23:56.972 --> 23:59.154
He says, I'm the real manna.

23:59.970 --> 24:08.325
You might look back to that daily miracle of frosted flakes and the wilderness that your ancestors enjoyed, but I want you to know that that was pointing to something else.

24:09.046 --> 24:10.068
That was pointing to me.

24:11.049 --> 24:15.377
And I am the true soul-satisfying bread that God has sent.

24:18.643 --> 24:21.808
So how do we feed on this man and this bread from heaven?

24:21.828 --> 24:22.930
What does that mean?

24:24.706 --> 24:27.971
Well, I think it begins with an act of surrender and trust.

24:27.991 --> 24:31.556
You remember that God has said there was a test embedded in the manna.

24:32.538 --> 24:34.461
It was a trust test.

24:35.482 --> 24:39.548
Would they believe that he would provide what they needed?

24:40.930 --> 24:44.435
Would they give up trying to find contentment on their own terms?

24:46.639 --> 24:54.290
See, when it comes to leaning on our own plans, our own priorities, there has to come a point for each one of us where we say, enough.

24:55.682 --> 25:00.549
Enough trying to satisfy my deepest longings with things that keep coming up empty.

25:02.011 --> 25:16.994
Enough telling myself the same lies or listening to the lies my culture keeps telling me that the next new thing, the next new relationship, the next new promotion, the next pay raise, the next, the next, the next is ever going to be enough.

25:18.816 --> 25:22.642
Do we finally say I can't get no satisfaction

25:23.266 --> 25:27.892
in all of those things that I've poured so much of my energy and time and priorities into.

25:27.932 --> 25:33.099
And that's not just a word for those who have never yet chosen to follow Jesus.

25:33.119 --> 25:37.384
In John's revelation, there are messages directed to seven different churches.

25:37.444 --> 25:41.509
In essence, these are open letters to all churches, to all of God's people.

25:42.531 --> 25:45.154
Here's the open letter that was addressed to the church at Ephesus.

25:46.636 --> 25:51.442
I know your works, your toil, your patient endurance, but I have this against you.

25:52.130 --> 25:55.955
that you have abandoned the love you had at first.

25:57.297 --> 26:01.782
It says, you're good people, you're doing good things, and yet you're living with distracted hearts.

26:04.105 --> 26:10.834
You love Jesus, but over time, other things have been permitted to take a greater tug on your affections.

26:12.977 --> 26:17.042
See, Satan doesn't need us living in open rebellion.

26:18.146 --> 26:22.410
His aims can be met just as well with distractions and misplaced priorities.

26:23.691 --> 26:26.254
As long as our lives are wasted, that's all he cares about.

26:26.274 --> 26:31.739
And he can keep us looking for something that won't truly satisfy.

26:31.779 --> 26:33.561
He's got what he wants.

26:34.982 --> 26:37.285
Every Israelite was on the greatest journey of their life.

26:37.385 --> 26:40.668
They had been set free by a literal miracle of God's grace.

26:41.969 --> 26:45.272
The fiery cloud, the manifestation of God's spirit was leading them.

26:45.333 --> 26:46.834
They were being provided.

26:47.074 --> 26:55.308
day by day with everything that they needed, that every reason to be satisfied people and yet.

26:57.312 --> 27:01.539
Now the rabble that was among them had a strong craving.

27:02.381 --> 27:06.428
And the people of Israel also wept again and said, oh, that we had meat to eat.

27:07.009 --> 27:09.874
We remember the fish we eat in Egypt that cost nothing

27:10.082 --> 27:18.912
The cucumbers, the melons, the leeks, the onions, the garlic, but now our strength is dried up and there's nothing at all but this manna to look at.

27:18.932 --> 27:23.617
The rabble and their strong cravings.

27:25.479 --> 27:29.183
They get already fired up and suddenly everybody is weeping.

27:30.244 --> 27:30.745
Weeping.

27:31.926 --> 27:33.688
Wow, remember the free food?

27:34.969 --> 27:36.471
Oh, you could eat cucumbers.

27:37.352 --> 27:39.154
Man, those were the good old days.

27:41.506 --> 27:47.034
Now, it does leave out one tiny detail about free food, which was you do recall you were slaves.

27:48.416 --> 27:52.202
There was a price attached to those things that you were craving.

27:54.265 --> 27:57.150
Scripture talks about the things that can draw us aside.

27:57.170 --> 27:58.672
It talks about the world, right?

27:58.712 --> 28:10.770
The cultural influences around us, or the flesh, our own internal cravings, and the devil, our spiritual enemy, that try to convince us that our momentary cravings are essentials.

28:11.394 --> 28:18.003
And at the same time, try to get us to ignore the price that those cravings made demand.

28:20.206 --> 28:22.910
I love what they say, our strength is dried up.

28:24.192 --> 28:25.453
Doesn't that just break your heart?

28:26.755 --> 28:28.658
We are wasting away to nothing here, man.

28:29.339 --> 28:31.221
We just got to have some free onions.

28:31.321 --> 28:32.142
That would do it.

28:34.386 --> 28:40.594
I was about 12 years old as I recall when my family had gone to Victoria and we had lunch at this restaurant.

28:40.962 --> 28:45.690
The waitress came to our table and she heard me saying, I'm starving.

28:47.132 --> 28:50.418
And her reply was, oh, you're not starving honey.

28:51.720 --> 28:53.062
Now at the time it made me mad.

28:54.184 --> 28:56.889
I felt as being disrespected here at the restaurant, you know?

28:58.672 --> 28:59.433
But she was right.

29:01.837 --> 29:02.979
My knees were fully met.

29:03.179 --> 29:04.722
I was not starving.

29:05.602 --> 29:11.091
What it was was a ploy to try and get my parents to give me something more that I wanted.

29:12.894 --> 29:18.603
Exaggeration, catastrophizing, rationalizing.

29:18.643 --> 29:29.441
Those are all things that we also easily fall prey to, to try and create a reason why we should get our cravings met.

29:29.922 --> 29:31.304
I have to have this.

29:31.364 --> 29:32.626
If I don't get this,

29:32.706 --> 29:33.908
My strength is dried up.

29:34.088 --> 29:36.371
I'm going to die if I don't get this."

29:38.353 --> 29:39.755
You know, the rabble is still here, right?

29:40.757 --> 29:46.304
The world, the flesh, the devil are still out there promoting cravings as essentials.

29:48.026 --> 29:51.771
Years ago, I decided to quit subscribing to computer magazines.

29:51.851 --> 29:57.138
I used to get several, and every issue was dedicated to convincing me

29:57.250 --> 30:02.075
that what I already had was too old and too slow and too limited.

30:02.095 --> 30:04.058
I needed to buy the next generation.

30:05.659 --> 30:07.141
I needed more.

30:08.082 --> 30:10.104
And man, I had all the rationalizations.

30:10.585 --> 30:11.626
I had all the reasons.

30:11.706 --> 30:17.813
I mean, I probably won't be able to work this week or get anything done if I don't get a new computer.

30:19.575 --> 30:25.682
So I finally decided to stop taking the magazines because they just kept drawing me in to I got a half.

30:27.042 --> 30:29.645
Of course, magazine subscriptions are so 1990.

30:29.685 --> 30:48.468
And in the age of big data, there are massive companies who are analyzing every online click and swipe and targeting advertising to me that is directly tailored to the cravings it has identified in my life.

30:50.210 --> 30:53.554
To try and make me believe that that is what I need for true fulfillment.

30:55.042 --> 30:57.726
But it's not just big data centers that play on my cravings.

30:57.886 --> 30:58.727
Scripture is clear.

30:58.767 --> 31:02.052
We have a spiritual enemy who plays our cravings as well.

31:03.173 --> 31:05.417
It's a game that goes back as far as the Garden of Eden.

31:06.899 --> 31:07.399
Don't you know?

31:07.459 --> 31:08.921
Did you eat that fruit?

31:09.823 --> 31:10.484
You'll have more.

31:11.345 --> 31:12.486
You'll be like, God.

31:13.728 --> 31:17.013
And so that craving is awakened, and yet it was a lie.

31:18.615 --> 31:23.602
Part of the lesson of manna was to teach the people daily dependence on God's provision

31:23.682 --> 31:27.225
not to consume themselves with worry about tomorrow.

31:28.186 --> 31:30.628
Another part was to teach the discipline of contentment.

31:30.649 --> 31:35.413
They had all they needed, but not necessarily all that they wanted or craved.

31:36.714 --> 31:41.339
Maybe you remember years ago, Keith Green had his album, so you want to go back to Egypt.

31:42.079 --> 31:44.802
And it's all about his journey from Egypt.

31:44.922 --> 31:53.650
And the key song, so you want to go back to Egypt, he rifts about the discontent that Israelites had from eating manna every day.

31:54.114 --> 31:58.480
And he imagines all the ways that they might have served manna over 40 years.

31:58.620 --> 31:59.701
Maybe you remember this.

32:00.663 --> 32:10.235
Manna waffles, manna burgers, manna bagels, fillet of manna, manna patty, and then the crux of it all, bamana bread.

32:15.182 --> 32:16.263
So how is your contentment?

32:18.146 --> 32:21.170
Have you surrendered your discontent to Jesus?

32:22.434 --> 32:26.141
Are you willing to gratefully receive what he provides?

32:28.845 --> 32:30.168
What are the cucumbers that tempt you?

32:33.433 --> 32:40.385
If we're gonna feed and satisfy our souls in Jesus, I think we have to take steps to stop filling our souls with junk food.

32:42.048 --> 32:43.531
Don't fall for free cucumbers.

32:45.334 --> 32:47.538
Second thing I would say is we need to be in his word.

32:48.258 --> 32:59.510
Colossians chapter three says this, let the word of Christ dwell in you richly, teaching and admonishing one another in all wisdom, singing songs and hymns and spiritual songs with thankfulness in your hearts to God.

32:59.550 --> 33:06.518
And whatever you do in word or deed, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.

33:06.538 --> 33:13.586
And you notice that he encourages them to let the word of Christ dwell in them richly.

33:14.882 --> 33:20.270
You should just dwell on that phrase for a little bit, but what does that mean to let God's word dwell in you richly?

33:20.350 --> 33:22.133
It goes beyond just reading it.

33:23.154 --> 33:26.960
Okay, that's kind of the Costco-free sample wave coming at God's word.

33:27.000 --> 33:30.365
You know, just grab a bite, that seems interesting, and then moving on.

33:30.805 --> 33:32.648
So don't let it dwell in you.

33:32.668 --> 33:34.691
In fact, don't just study it.

33:35.031 --> 33:42.322
You can study God's word in a very academic way, get lots of facts, and it hasn't really yet dwelt in you.

33:43.170 --> 33:51.178
I think that's probably the reason why Jesus, when he instituted the Lord's Supper, he gave them something bread and a cup that they internalized.

33:51.919 --> 34:01.368
He said, you need to internalize who I am, what I teach, my priorities, a walk with my spirit needs to become part of you.

34:04.111 --> 34:07.814
Some people treat scripture like some kids play with food on their plate.

34:07.835 --> 34:11.378
It's intriguing, they push it around, but they never actually take it in.

34:12.418 --> 34:26.223
That Paul told his young friend Timothy that there were people who would be always learning and never able to come to a knowledge of the truth, just collecting facts, but it never actually becomes something that changes the way they live.

34:28.948 --> 34:31.192
So here are some very practical suggestions.

34:32.875 --> 34:34.738
First, I would say read.

34:36.162 --> 34:37.604
You need to read God's word.

34:37.644 --> 34:39.866
You're not going to get it just by osmosis, okay?

34:40.187 --> 34:46.214
Holding your Bible in your hand or laying your hand on your phone app is not going to get God's word in your life.

34:46.234 --> 34:47.796
You actually have to read it for yourself.

34:48.717 --> 34:53.343
And what you might just do is pick a passage of Scripture and make it your passage of the week.

34:54.304 --> 34:57.688
Again, I appreciate programs that try and get you to read through the Bible in a year.

34:58.489 --> 34:59.510
Nothing wrong with that.

35:00.151 --> 35:06.098
But if you've ever done it, you know that sometimes you're more intent on getting through today's assignment than you are actually

35:06.178 --> 35:07.780
taking in what the word is saying.

35:08.982 --> 35:10.344
You don't need to read even a whole chapter.

35:10.484 --> 35:11.145
Pick a verse.

35:11.625 --> 35:11.946
Read it.

35:12.046 --> 35:13.328
Make it the verse for the week.

35:14.149 --> 35:14.830
Write it down.

35:15.110 --> 35:16.732
Post it where you can see it during the day.

35:16.792 --> 35:22.460
Take a single verse and read the verses around it so you get the context.

35:23.622 --> 35:27.187
If there's something that's hard for you to understand, we'll go find a commentary and check it out.

35:28.248 --> 35:29.650
But read God's word.

35:31.234 --> 35:34.878
or maybe some devotional literature would help you if you don't know where to start.

35:35.739 --> 35:42.508
One of the things that we have available, speaking of manna, well devotional has been around for years.

35:42.848 --> 35:45.952
New one comes out once a quarter called our daily bread.

35:46.713 --> 35:49.276
Every day has a scripture, has a thought about it.

35:49.776 --> 35:51.118
This is a great place to start.

35:51.158 --> 35:55.804
If you don't have a daily discipline of being God's word, this will get you started.

35:58.587 --> 36:01.010
First, there are a lot of apps on your phone that will help you with that.

36:01.442 --> 36:16.019
You version if you go there has lots of devotional resources available Find a way to create that discipline like the children of Israel that were to collect manna every day All right, sometimes we get it backwards They were supposed to collect enough.

36:16.039 --> 36:23.988
They didn't need to collect anything on the Sabbath Some of us just come to church once a week very well get everything we need for the week and move on from there It's sort of backwards.

36:24.429 --> 36:28.754
He says daily being God's word the second thing I would say is pray

36:29.314 --> 36:32.459
Ask the Holy Spirit to teach you as you meditate on a passage.

36:33.481 --> 36:35.043
A third thing I would say is memorize.

36:35.764 --> 36:38.128
Commit scripture to memory so it becomes part of you.

36:38.188 --> 36:40.272
My wife is real musical.

36:40.352 --> 36:43.176
Sometimes she has set scripture to music and sing it.

36:43.897 --> 36:44.598
That's good for her.

36:44.639 --> 36:46.622
For me, it might not be as edifying if I sing it.

36:47.062 --> 36:52.191
But whatever it takes, bring God's word in so you can dwell on it.

36:53.152 --> 36:53.773
Meditate.

36:54.955 --> 36:56.818
Consider what the words have to teach you.

36:57.730 --> 37:00.353
And jot down the thoughts that God begins to impress on your mind.

37:00.394 --> 37:06.922
That's what I've been encouraging you to do in keeping this travel logs we go through is begin to write and think and pray through God's word.

37:08.684 --> 37:10.587
The Israelites had to collect manna daily.

37:11.869 --> 37:17.035
Our intentional engagement with Jesus needs to be a daily practice.

37:17.055 --> 37:19.058
And do you see what's happening if you do this?

37:19.810 --> 37:29.381
If you do this, you are chewing, you are thinking, you are internalizing, you are spiritually feeding on and being shaped by God's Word.

37:30.122 --> 37:33.125
You are letting the Word dwell in you richly.

37:34.506 --> 37:37.069
Next thing I would suggest is you need to be in fellowship.

37:37.089 --> 37:40.253
You notice that Paul talks about all this in the context of one another.

37:40.293 --> 37:42.535
Feeding on Christ is a group activity.

37:43.697 --> 37:48.402
Whenever you see the Lord's table being observed in the New Testament, you see people sharing it together.

37:48.962 --> 37:55.232
I'm convinced that's one of the things is key to the vitality of our church body that so many of you are in life groups.

37:55.933 --> 37:57.396
You're in Bible study groups together.

37:57.436 --> 38:01.763
You are helping each other to let the word dwell in you richly.

38:03.285 --> 38:05.509
And then I would say we need to be in obedience.

38:06.250 --> 38:11.899
The Lord told Moses that part of the man in part was a test to see if his people would obey him.

38:13.001 --> 38:15.986
Jesus repeatedly said his true followers were people who both

38:16.130 --> 38:19.115
occurred and obeyed his words.

38:20.697 --> 38:29.972
Paul's counsel for believers to teach and admonish one another has that idea where we are together helping each other to grow up in Christ.

38:32.055 --> 38:39.026
James said the real proof of those who claim to have faith is that they do the things that Jesus is asking them to do.

38:41.506 --> 38:46.311
You know what the evidence was as to whether or not an Israelite who claimed faithful to God really was?

38:46.351 --> 38:49.954
It was the kind of smell that was coming out of his tent.

38:52.196 --> 38:56.520
You could tell it in 24 hours if he was doing what God had asked him to do.

38:58.422 --> 39:06.890
If the neighbor's tent had the aroma of three-day old roadkill, it wasn't hard to figure out that maybe his words and his actions weren't lining up.

39:08.892 --> 39:10.674
I must say there are a lot of people in this world

39:11.618 --> 39:21.272
who are pretty turned off to Jesus because of the smells that come from the tents of some of the people that claim to be his followers.

39:23.115 --> 39:27.542
The words they hear and the actions they see don't line up.

39:29.124 --> 39:35.554
And that stink causes them to say, I don't want anything to do with that Jesus.

39:37.677 --> 39:38.418
Obedience.

39:40.578 --> 39:42.100
What smells are coming from your tent?

39:44.082 --> 39:45.183
And then I'd say be in prayer.

39:46.545 --> 39:57.056
Paul sees this constant river of Thanksgiving as being an important part of the Christian life rather than dwelling in and feasting on our complaints and our disappointments in a broken world.

39:57.637 --> 40:06.306
To dwelling Christ means that we are engaging the discipline of thankfulness, which goes hand in hand with contentment, right?

40:06.326 --> 40:09.650
Remember that the rabble out there in the wilderness and they're going, oh man,

40:10.370 --> 40:15.837
Man, if we just had some free onions, some more cucumbers, man, then life would truly be great.

40:16.138 --> 40:22.747
Instead of being thankful that God had provided for them in a place where they should have starved to death, their needs were met.

40:23.608 --> 40:28.755
Instead of Thanksgiving, their lives became characterized by discontent and complaining.

40:31.438 --> 40:40.050
Prayer is a place where we can begin to reign in those cravings and give thanks to God for what he has done for us.

40:42.146 --> 40:43.407
One more observation on manna.

40:45.209 --> 40:48.753
There was a day when the manna stopped coming.

40:50.194 --> 40:57.862
Here's Joshua's account of what happened on the first Sabbath that was celebrated in Canaan, their journey's promised destination.

40:59.243 --> 41:03.267
And the manna ceased the day after the eight of the produce of the land.

41:04.148 --> 41:10.034
And there was no longer manna for the people of Israel, but they ate the fruit of the land of Canaan that year.

41:11.362 --> 41:16.267
See, all through the long journey home, God had miraculously provided and sustained His people.

41:17.509 --> 41:21.133
The wilderness they were in could never satisfy their deepest yearnings.

41:22.174 --> 41:28.020
The manna sustained them and to have abandoned it for the cravings would have taken them back into slavery.

41:29.622 --> 41:31.123
But the manna was not the goal.

41:32.705 --> 41:34.987
It was simply the provision to get them home.

41:36.589 --> 41:41.074
In Paul's first letter to the Corinthian church, he has a lot to say about the importance of love.

41:41.218 --> 41:42.600
especially in chapter 13.

41:42.680 --> 41:48.729
And to truly love Jesus said, summed up everything that Moses and the prophets had ever commanded.

41:49.710 --> 41:52.274
To love God with all of your heart, soul, and being.

41:53.075 --> 41:54.497
To love your neighbor as yourself.

41:56.279 --> 42:02.028
And Paul doesn't deny in the slightest that God does miraculous things to sustain and guide his people.

42:02.789 --> 42:09.298
But he emphasizes that greater than a miracle is a centrality of love in a Christian's life.

42:10.946 --> 42:12.829
And he concludes his thoughts with these words.

42:14.933 --> 42:15.754
Love never ends.

42:17.177 --> 42:19.260
As for prophecies, they will pass away.

42:20.242 --> 42:22.205
As for tongues, they will cease.

42:23.087 --> 42:25.291
As for knowledge, it will pass away.

42:25.932 --> 42:29.458
Talking about God's miraculous manifestations of power to the people.

42:30.419 --> 42:34.226
He says, because when the perfect comes, the partial will pass away.

42:35.202 --> 42:38.387
Now we see in the mirror dimly, but then face to face.

42:38.707 --> 42:42.833
Now I know in part, then I shall know fully, even as I've been fully known.

42:43.394 --> 42:47.981
So now the journey here, faith, hope, and love abide.

42:48.061 --> 42:48.762
These three.

42:49.763 --> 42:52.667
But the greatest of these is love.

42:54.490 --> 43:02.642
Someday we won't need the manna of faith and hope because we will see Jesus face to face.

43:03.682 --> 43:05.364
We will be in His presence.

43:07.145 --> 43:11.370
But Paul says, man, the greatest of it all is love.

43:12.771 --> 43:18.296
That people would see in our lives that we love God, that we are walking with Him.

43:19.838 --> 43:24.262
And the one of the ways they would see it is because they see the love that comes out of us toward other people.

43:26.464 --> 43:26.885
Let's pray.

43:30.689 --> 43:32.210
Father, forgive us for

43:33.890 --> 43:39.719
The many times that we set our eyes our affections on the free cucumbers of life.

43:40.941 --> 43:55.122
We trade away the riches of contentment and life in you for the things that our world is putting in front of us that offer to make us fuller people, richer people, and yet come up empty every time.

43:57.485 --> 44:03.314
Lord, I pray for any of my friends here today that have never yet entered into a relationship with you.

44:04.546 --> 44:10.593
And I pray that you would open their hearts and eyes to see that in you are the things that they truly most deeply desire.

44:10.753 --> 44:18.841
And for those of us who have started the journey of following you, Father forgive us for the places we've taken our eyes off of you.

44:19.062 --> 44:24.287
Forgive us for the times that we have been discontented and not grateful.

44:25.549 --> 44:27.411
Or give us hearts I pray full of thanks.

44:29.373 --> 44:34.098
And may the aroma that comes out of our life be an aroma that is sweet.

44:35.010 --> 44:41.232
that is attractive because people see our great love for you and our great love for them.

44:41.272 --> 44:45.026
And I asked this in Jesus' powerful name.

44:45.889 --> 44:46.290
Amen.

